  "result": "**Rebase** rewrites history: it takes your commits and replays them on top of the target branch, producing a linear history with new commit SHAs.\n\n**Merge** preserves history: it creates a merge commit that ties the two branch tips together, keeping the original commits and their timestamps intact.\n\nKey tradeoffs:\n- **Rebase** → clean linear log, but rewrites SHAs (never rebase shared/public branches without coordination).\n- **Merge** → safe for shared branches, but log becomes a DAG with merge commits.\n\nRule of thumb: rebase local/private work before sharing; merge when integrating into shared branches.",
